SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c01961950
Version: 1

HPSBTU02496 SSRT090245 rev.1 - HP Tru64 UNIX Running NTP, Denial of Service (DoS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2010-10-04
Last Updated: 2010-10-04

Potential Security Impact: Denial of Service (DoS)

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified on the HP Tru64 Operating System when running NTP Server. The vulnerability could be remotely exploited to create a Denial of Service (DoS).

References: CVE-2009-3563

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
Tru64 UNIX v 5.1B-5 (BL28) running NTP
Tru64 UNIX v 5.1B-4 (BL27) running NTP

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2009-3563    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:P)       6.4
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP is releasing the following setld-based patch kits to resolve the vulnerability.

